"""You can see the description of the task using the code specified in the title on leetcode.
This program has O(1) complexity by time and O(1) by space.

It is most advantageous to split the number into n-1 and 1 to minimize the cost, which will equal n-1. 
We then repeat the process with the remaining part, yielding 5, 4, 3...; 
the cost decreases in step with the number itself, and the total cost simply becomes the sum of an arithmetic progression.
It is so pleasant to look back on the school mathematics.
"""

class Solution:
    def minCost(self, n: int) -> int:
        return int((n - 1) / 2 * n)
        
